node.text:
I’m in love with this cross. She can be a sassy little thing but I love her. I’ll be popping more of these seeds I made to find a more stable selection. This plant isn’t perfect yet but she’s perfect to me. My work will continue with her. 
Cake Crasher x Stardawg IX

node.text:
The Spanish Moon project is coming along nicely. The seeds have been made and I’m growing them now to see what’s in there. I crossed Spanish Moon into several plants for various reasons and I’m beyond excited to share my findings soon enough. I know there’s a lot of you as excited as I am about this project, and it is testing all of our patience! Lol. Let’s cross our fingers and toes that these plants are as special as I believe they are going to be🤞
Well over a year of my time, love and attention has gone into this one💚

node.text:
Here’s a bud that was taken right before harvest and placed in an aero cloner. I posted a bud shot with roots the other day. 
Once I have roots, I put the clone in a 1/2 gallon pot with soil (as pictured). Slide through the 3 pictures I posted showing the progression of the reveg. You can leave the bud on or cut it off at this point. It’s personal preference. 18-24 hours of light, all of it works. Find a preference that works for your personal situation. You can also flower this plant again, or simply clone from the reveg. 
In life, you lose things or people you love and there’s nothing you can do about it. In this case, you can love a plant and keep it alive. It’s one of the rare exceptions that life provides and I think it’s pretty dang cool! 
#Reveg #DontLoseAPlantYouLove

node.text: Here’s another way I re veg. Revegging is not my first choice but sometimes it’s the only choice. When I love a genetic so much that I just can’t lose it, I do 2 things. One was a previous post (a couple days ago) and I also do this. The thought of losing a genetic that I love terrifies me and breaks my heart. So, I reveg the whole pot, or I do this tech. I simply take a clone from the most fleshy underneath part of the plant  and put it in my aero cloner. Shockingly, they root in 4-7 days which is generally faster than the average clone. Once rooted, I place clone in soil and water lightly for weeks to come. Slowly but surely, this plant will grow new vegetative growth directly out of the bud! It’s pretty cool to watch. Just one more amazing thing this plant can do. We’re so dang lucky to be able to geek out on , and grow this plant. #Grateful
